    <section class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-{{ section.id }}">
      <svg class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-eye-{{ section.id }}" viewBox="0 0 800 280" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M45 140C132 51 261 15 400 15C539 15 668 51 755 140C668 229 539 265 400 265C261 265 132 229 45 140Z" stroke="#C9A84C" stroke-opacity="0.35" stroke-width="2"/>
        <circle cx="400" cy="140" r="46" stroke="#C9A84C" stroke-opacity="0.35" stroke-width="2"/>
        <circle cx="400" cy="140" r="10" fill="#C9A84C" fill-opacity="0.5"/>
      </svg>

      <div class="v2-what-is-iris__label-{{ section.id }}">What is IRIS</div>
      <h1 class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-title-{{ section.id }}">
        The physical object.
        <em>The digital memory.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-body-{{ section.id }}">
        A hand-finished artwork. Real gold inside. A chip that remembers. A number that is yours alone.
        This is what IRIS is — before it is anything else.
      </p>

      <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-specs-{{ section.id }}">
        <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-{{ section.id }}">
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-value-{{ section.id }}">4 x 4</div>
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-label-{{ section.id }}">Format</div>
        </div>
        <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-{{ section.id }}">
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-value-{{ section.id }}">0.4g</div>
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-label-{{ section.id }}">Real gold</div>
        </div>
        <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-{{ section.id }}">
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-value-{{ section.id }}">NFC</div>
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-label-{{ section.id }}">Chip inside</div>
        </div>
        <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-{{ section.id }}">
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-value-{{ section.id }}">∞</div>
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__hero-spec-label-{{ section.id }}">Archived forever</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="v2-what-is-iris__scroll-{{ section.id }}">
        <span>Scroll</span>
        <div class="v2-what-is-iris__scroll-line-{{ section.id }}"></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="v2-what-is-iris__split-{{ section.id }}">
      <div class="v2-what-is-iris__split-left-{{ section.id }}">
        <span class="v2-what-is-iris__label-{{ section.id }}">I — The object</span>
        <h2>A physical thing.<br>Made by hand.<br><span class="v2-what-is-iris__gold-em-{{ section.id }}">Numbered.</span></h2>
        <p>IRIS is a 4 x 4 inch physical artwork on archival paper, mounted and framed by hand. Every piece is finished as a complete art object — not a print, not a certificate, not a placeholder.</p>
        <p>Inside each piece, embedded into the work itself: 0.4 grams of physical gold. Not applied to the surface. Inside. Part of what the work is made of.</p>
        <p>Each work is individually numbered, sealed, and prepared as a singular artifact. Small enough to hold in your hand. Finished enough to live on your wall.</p>

        <div class="v2-what-is-iris__object-specs-{{ section.id }}">
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__object-row-{{ section.id }}">
            <div class="v2-what-is-iris__object-key-{{ section.id }}">Format</div>
            <div class="v2-what-is-iris__object-value-{{ section.id }}">4 x 4 inches · archival paper · framed</div>
          </div>
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__object-row-{{ section.id }}">
            <div class="v2-what-is-iris__object-key-{{ section.id }}">Gold</div>
            <div class="v2-what-is-iris__object-value-{{ section.id }}">0.4g physical gold · embedded</div>
          </div>
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__object-row-{{ section.id }}">
            <div class="v2-what-is-iris__object-key-{{ section.id }}">Finish</div>
            <div class="v2-what-is-iris__object-value-{{ section.id }}">Hand-finished · numbered · sealed</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

