          <rect x="104" y="104" width="132" height="132" fill="#10100e" stroke="#3a3830"/>
          <path d="M170 132C188 132 202 148 202 170C202 192 188 208 170 208C152 208 138 192 138 170C138 148 152 132 170 132Z" fill="none" stroke="#e8e4dc" stroke-width="2"/>
          <path d="M136 170C146 152 157 144 170 144C183 144 194 152 204 170" fill="none" stroke="#e8e4dc" stroke-width="2"/>
          <circle cx="240" cy="102" r="9" fill="#c9a84c" opacity="0.9"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="v2-what-is-iris__split-{{ section.id }} v2-what-is-iris__split-{{ section.id }}--dark">
      <div class="v2-what-is-iris__gold-visual-{{ section.id }}">
        <div class="v2-what-is-iris__rings-wrap-{{ section.id }}">
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__ring-{{ section.id }} v2-what-is-iris__ring-{{ section.id }}--one"></div>
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__ring-{{ section.id }} v2-what-is-iris__ring-{{ section.id }}--two"></div>
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__ring-{{ section.id }} v2-what-is-iris__ring-{{ section.id }}--three"></div>
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__sphere-{{ section.id }}"></div>
          <div class="v2-what-is-iris__gold-weight-{{ section.id }}">
            <span class="v2-what-is-iris__gold-weight-num-{{ section.id }}">0.4g</span>
            <span class="v2-what-is-iris__gold-weight-label-{{ section.id }}">Physical gold · per piece · live price</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="v2-what-is-iris__gold-copy-{{ section.id }}">
        <span class="v2-what-is-iris__label-{{ section.id }}">II — The gold</span>
        <h2 class="v2-what-is-iris__split-left-{{ section.id }}-title">Not symbolic.<br>Not decorative.<br><span class="v2-what-is-iris__gold-em-{{ section.id }}">Real.</span></h2>
        <p>Every IRIS contains 0.4 grams of physical gold — embedded into the work itself. You can feel the weight. It is not applied to the surface, not printed, not approximated. It is there.</p>
        <p>Gold has been a measure of value for five thousand years. In a world of digital assets and abstract instruments, the gold inside IRIS returns to something elemental and irreducible: a material reality.</p>
        <p>The price of IRIS is tied to the live gold market. As gold moves, so does the minimum price of each piece. The value is not invented — it is anchored.</p>
        <blockquote class="v2-what-is-iris__blockquote-{{ section.id }}">A trace of permanence in every piece.</blockquote>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="v2-what-is-iris__split-{{ section.id }}">
      <div class="v2-what-is-iris__split-left-{{ section.id }}">
        <span class="v2-what-is-iris__label-{{ section.id }}">III — The identity</span>
        <h2>Every piece<br>knows<br><span class="v2-what-is-iris__gold-em-{{ section.id }}">who it belongs to.</span></h2>
        <p>Inside the frame, an NFC chip. The moment you scan it, your piece awakens — its number, its artwork, its rarity, its position in the collection. All revealed at once.</p>
        <p>That activation is permanent. Your number enters the IRIS archive — a public record of every piece that has ever been revealed. It stays there. Forever.</p>
        <p>The archive is not a blockchain. It is a living registry — every scan, every owner, every city. A growing history of where IRIS pieces exist in the world.</p>
      </div>

